Osun state governor, Gboyega Oyetola, has signed the 2019 budget of N154, 406,541,400. The signing of the budget was witnessed by Speaker of the House of Assembly, Hon. Najeem Salam on Friday. Also, the Supervisor for Ministry of Budget and Economic Planning, Dr. Olalekan Yinusa and Supervisor for Finance, Mr. Bola Oyebamiji were at the event. The recurrent expenditure is N61,320,327,350 while the capital expenditure is N93,086,214,050 Daily Trust recalls that Governor Oyetola had laid the budget estimate before the lawmakers on December 27, 2018. Osun governor to present first budget on Thursday Osun gov. presents N152bn budget for 2019 PDP, Osun govt trade words over budget